# The "files" whitelist in package.json is the source of truth for what gets
# published. This .npmignore is a belt-and-suspenders guard so a binary that
# install.js downloads into bin/ during local testing is never accidentally
# published to npm. We ship only the launcher shim + installer, not the binary.

# Downloaded native binaries (any platform).
bin/bharatcode
bin/bharatcode.exe

# Local cruft.
*.tar.gz
*.zip
*.tgz
.DS_Store
node_modules/
INSTALL.md
